	</div><div class="blogs_entrybody" style="clear:both">
		If the age-old adage that "curiosity killed the cat" was true, I was one dead pussy.  <br/><br/>Stop snickering.My attention turned to a few other stacks of invoices and bills from the past few months and centered on the cell phone bills.  They were huge!  Each bill was carefully marked in the upper right hand corner with a name.  I quickly figured out that this was how Dana (or whoever was paying the bills) was attaching bills to employees of the company.  <br/><br/>Mark's cell phone bill was several pages thick with lots of calls to the MMM office and, according to the company phone list (which strangely enough had cell and home phone numbers listed as well), his brother.  Mike's cell phone bill was easily a third larger with very similar numbers.  One particular number seemed to repeat throughout the bill, and the call times varied between 18:00 hours and 02:00 hours.<br/><br/>"Unusual." I thought to myself.  <br/><br/>I flipped through the rest of the bills and made note of interesting companies and amounts.<br/><br/>"Boss." I heard Scrap say as he stood in the doorway of the office.<br/><br/>"Yo." I responded without taking my eyes off of my notepad.<br/><br/>"Cameras are up.  You want to check these guys out?" Scrap asked.<br/><br/>I peered up from my scribbling to see Scrap brush a few layers of drywall and ceiling tile dust from his shirt.<br/><br/>"I'm sure you have it under control.  You ready to image that workstation?" I queried as I noticed that my coffee level was approaching critical. <br/><br/>"Sure.  You want to set it up?" Scrap asked in an I-so-want-to-sit-down-and-rest tone.<br/><br/>I chuckled.<br/><br/>"Not a problem.  I think I have what I need here." I said as I placed the invoices and bills neatly back into organized piles.<br/><br/>We walked out to Dana's cubicle and started to unpack Roscoe.  I threw Scrap my trusty digital camera.<br/><br/>"Start snapping." I said with a smirk.<br/><br/>Scrap was not pleased.<br/><br/>After photographing the work area, we focused our attention on the workstation.  It was your average beige box PC with a Windows 2000 license sticker affixed neatly to the rear of the case.<br/><br/>"It's powered off." Scrap noted as pulled the workstation from its position on the desk.<br/><br/>After some masterful case removal by Scrap and more photographs, we snaked an IDE tap cable from Roscoe to the workstation's hard drive.<br/><br/>"Write blocker is in place.  Let's welcome Roscoe to another fun-filled adventure." I said as I powered up Roscoe.  <br/><br/>Well, I attempted to power up Roscoe.<br/><br/>"DAMN!" I screamed.  Roscoe was dead.<br/><br/>Scrap grabbed Roscoe and proceeded to initiate computer triage. <br/><br/>"Dude, that's the second power supply that has died in this guy.  What the hell?" Scrap said in disgust.<br/><br/>I dug through my bag of tools and software in despair and grabbed my trusty Encase boot disk.<br/><br/>"We're saved!" Scrap joked as he unhooked Roscoe and prepared to do a local capture on the workstation.<br/><br/>Scrap double-checked that the internal hard drive wasn't attached to the machine's IDE cable, inserted the boot disk, and pressed the power button.  He quickly hit the proper key and was looking at a BIOS screen.<br/><br/>"Date and time check out, booting from floppy ... looks like we're ready to do this." <br/><br/>I was daydreaming.<br/><br/>"Eh, Chief are you there?" Scrap asked as he waved his paws around in the air.<br/><br/>"555-0055" I said out loud.<br/><br/>"Is that a song?  I thought it was '8-6-7 ...'" Scrap joked.<br/><br/>"No, no, no.  I'll be right back.  Start the imaging." I barked as I walked back into the office and towards the piles of bills and invoices.<br/><br/>I flipped through Mike's cell phone records again and looked at the popular phone number, and the odd times that it was dialed.<br/><br/>Holding the cell phone records with one hand, I scanned the company phone directory for the phone number.<br/><br/>Mike and Dana must have had a lot to talk about.<br/><br/>At two o'clock in the morning?<br/><br/><hr><br/><p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707130414/http://www.numly.com/numly/verify.asp?id=21390-060502-131035-92"><img alt="esn" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707130414im_/http://numly.com/numly/icon.asp?id=2139006050213103592" border="0"> 21390-060502-131035-92</a> Rate content: <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707130414/http://numly.com/numly/verify.asp?id=2139006050213103592&amp;rate=yes"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707130414im_/http://numly.com/numly/thumbup.gif" border="0"></a><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707130414/http://numly.com/numly/verify.asp?id=2139006050213103592&amp;rate=no"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707130414im_/http://numly.com/numly/thumbdown.gif" border="0"></a><br><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707130414im_/http://numly.com/numly/barcode.asp?code=2139006050213103592&amp;height=20&amp;width=1&amp;mode=code39"><br><br>Â© 2006 All Rights Reserved.</p><br/><p><hr><table width="100%" bgcolor="#FFFFCC" cellpadding="9px">
<tr><td><img style="margin-right: 9px; float: left" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707130414im_/http://userimages.ittoolbox.com/user/s_610000.jpg"><b><font face="Arial" size="4">DID YOU KNOW?</b></font><font face="Arial" size="2"><p style="margin-top: 2px">You can read all of SecurityMonkey's case files! <br>Find them <b><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707130414/http://blogs.ittoolbox.com/security/investigator/archives/official-securitymonkey-case-file-index-14787">here</a></b>. <br><br>You can also read all of SecurityMonkey's <br>'Banana Cupboard' stories <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707130414/http://blogs.ittoolbox.com/security/investigator/archives/banana-cupboard-stories-index-25647">here</a>.  <br><br>You may not get a lot done for a few hours... or even days.</font><br><br>The reviews are in...<br><br><i>"Completely addictive... suspenseful and informative at the same time!"<br>"A mix of classic detective scripting, timing, and technology..."<br>"Cleverly injected humor makes these case files easy to read and hard to put down!"</i></td></tr></table><hr><p>
